xpense.",{"type":550,"xml:lang":391,"resp":454,"p":553},"((Chi-Rho)) Aurelios Rhestoutos e Zosime, acquistammo questa tomba a nostre spese.",{"type":555,"resp":454,"p":556},"commentary",{"_":557,"ref":558,"foreign":574},"This is a marble plaque and not a sarcophagus, which must have served to mark a “loculus”, according to the interpretation that J. and L. Robert (BE 1964 nr. 631) gave for a similar inscription from Catania, RAC 8 (1931) 122-25 = . This inscription attests to the purchase of the tomb by the deceased who are buried in it: the names of the deceased are followed by the verb , an expression indicating that the purchase was made at their own expense () and by the object (for  as the tomb, see AE 1996.0792 =  and Ferrua 1958: 172). It is possible that there was a reflexive pronoun in the lacuna of l. 6, as in other cases where the deceased purchased the grave for himself: IMusCatania 229 = . For the registration of the purchase of the tomb in Christian epitaphs, see Führer and Schultze (1907: 12-15) and Korhonen (2004: 108-110). The cognomen of the deceased must have been Restitutus but for such a form, see ICUR 19782. The name of the woman, , is attested in other inscriptions of the city (CIL 10.7016 = , IMusCatania 165 = ) and more in general of Sicily (LGPN 3A: 190).",[559,562,565,568,571],{"_":560,"target":561},"ISic001547","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001547",{"_":563,"target":564},"ISic001423","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001423",{"_":566,"target":567},"ISic001628","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001628",{"_":569,"target":570},"ISic000300","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000300",{"_":572,"target":573},"ISic001649","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001649",[575,577,579,581],{"_":576,"xml:lang":112},"ἀγοράω",{"_":578,"xml:lang":112},"ἐκ τῶν ἰδίων",{"_":580,"xml:lang":112},"ἔνβασις",{"_":504,"xml:lang":112},{"type":583,"listBibl":584},"bibliography",[585,616],{"typ